{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775876761058,"sessionID":"ses_28580b4d1ffeK0mAmYw8p10j2Z","part":{"id":"prt_d7a80e5b5001mp4Hb15SpQXg3G","messageID":"msg_d7a80cce3001Z4V7MoYC1P3Z8v","sessionID":"ses_28580b4d1ffeK0mAmYw8p10j2Z","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-d7a4b376a0634dc19a1668d1a2dcfd25","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Specification — CLI pack Command\n2: \n3: AR: AR-020 — CLI pack 命令\n4: Module: cmd/cli\n5: Language: Python\n6: Size: M\n7: \n8: ---\n9: \n10: ## Requirement: Pack Command Entry Point\n11: \n12: The system SHALL provide a `pack` subcommand via Typer application to validate and prepare a workspace, merge CLI overrides into metadata, optionally generate a Dockerfile, and report paths.\n13: \n14: ### Scenario: Options and Defaults\n15: \n16: - **GIVEN** the user runs `pack` without specifying any options\n17: - **WHEN** the command is invoked\n18: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL use the following defaults:\n19:   - `workspace` = \".\" (`-f` / `--workspace`, type `str`)\n20:   - `agent_name` = `None` (`--agent-name`, type `Optional[str]`)\n21:   - `language` = `None` (`--language`, type `Optional[str]`)\n22:   - `entrypoint` = `None` (`--entrypoint`, type `Optional[str]`)\n23:   - `port` = `None` (`--port`, type `Optional[int]`)\n24:   - `build_mode` = `None` (`--build-mode`, type `Optional[str]`)\n25:   - `description` = `None` (`--description`, type `Optional[str]`)\n26:   - `output` = `None` (`--output`, type `Optional[str]`)\n27:   - `verbose` = `False` (`--verbose`, type `bool`)\n28: \n29: ### Scenario: Successful Pack\n30: \n31: - **GIVEN** a valid workspace path with required files for the specified language\n32: - **WHEN** `pack` completes without exception\n33: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL:\n34:   - Display a Rich Progress spinner during execution\n35:   - Print success message including `agent_name`, resolved `workspace_path`, and `metadata_path`\n36:   - Report `metadata_path` as `{final_workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml`\n37: \n38: ### Scenario: Pack Failure Handling with Verbose\n39: \n40: - **GIVEN** `PackRuntime.pack` raises an exception\n41: - **WHEN** `verbose` is `True`\n42: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL:\n43:   - Print `Error packaging agent: {e}` in red\n44:   - Print the full traceback\n45:   - Exit with code `1`\n46: \n47: ### Scenario: Pack Failure Handling without Verbose\n48: \n49: - **GIVEN** `PackRuntime.pack` raises an exception\n50: - **WHEN** `verbose` is `False`\n51: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL:\n52:   - Print `Error packaging agent: {e}` in red\n53:   - Exit with code `1` without printing traceback\n54: \n55: ---\n56: \n57: ## Requirement: Workspace Validation\n58: \n59: The system SHALL validate that the workspace path exists, is a directory, and contains language-specific required files.\n60: \n61: ### Scenario: Missing Workspace Directory\n62: \n63: - **GIVEN** the `workspace_path` does not exist on the filesystem\n64: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._validate_workspace_structure` runs\n65: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with a message indicating the directory does not exist\n66: \n67: ### Scenario: Workspace is Not a Directory\n68: \n69: - **GIVEN** the `workspace_path` exists but is not a directory\n70: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._validate_workspace_structure` runs\n71: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with a message indicating the path is not a directory\n72: \n73: ### Scenario: Python Workspace Without Python Files\n74: \n75: - **GIVEN** `metadata.language == \"python\"` and the workspace is a valid directory\n76: - **WHEN** no `*.py` files exist in the workspace root\n77: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")`\n78: \n79: ### Scenario: Java Workspace Without pom.xml\n80: \n81: - **GIVEN** `metadata.language == \"java\"` and the workspace is a valid directory\n82: - **WHEN** no `pom.xml` file exists in the workspace\n83: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` indicating `pom.xml` is required for Java projects\n84: \n85: ---\n86: \n87: ## Requirement: Metadata Loading and Creation\n88: \n89: The system SHALL load existing metadata from YAML or create new metadata with defaults when the file does not exist.\n90: \n91: ### Scenario: Load Existing Metadata from Primary File\n92: \n93: - **GIVEN** `{workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml` exists\n94: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._load_or_create_metadata` runs\n95: - **THEN** the system SHALL load metadata from `agent_metadata.yaml` and parse as `AgentMetadata`\n96: \n97: ### Scenario: Load Existing Metadata from Fallback Files\n98: \n99: - **GIVEN** `agent_metadata.yaml` does not exist but `agent.yaml` exists\n100: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._load_or_create_metadata` runs\n101: - **THEN** the system SHALL load metadata from `agent.yaml`\n102: \n103: ### Scenario: Load Existing Metadata from Secondary Fallback\n104: \n105: - **GIVEN** neither `agent_metadata.yaml` nor `agent.yaml` exists but `metadata.yaml` exists\n106: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._load_or_create_metadata` runs\n107: - **THEN** the system SHALL load metadata from `metadata.yaml`\n108: \n109: ### Scenario: Create New Metadata When No File Exists\n110: \n111: - **GIVEN** none of `agent_metadata.yaml`, `agent.yaml`, or `metadata.yaml` exist\n112: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._load_or_create_metadata` runs\n113: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n114:   - Create a new `AgentMetadata` with default values\n115:   - Set `agent_name` from CLI option or infer from workspace directory name\n116:   - Set `language` from CLI option or default to \"python\"\n117:   - Set `port` from CLI option or default to `8080`\n118:   - Set `build_mode` from CLI option or default to \"local\"\n119: \n120: ---\n121: \n122: ## Requirement: Option Overrides\n123: \n124: The system SHALL merge CLI option overrides into loaded or created metadata.\n125: \n126: ### Scenario: Override Agent Name\n127: \n128: - **GIVEN** metadata exists with `agent_name = \"original-name\"`\n129: - **WHEN** CLI option `--agent-name \"new-name\"` is provided\n130: - **THEN** `PackRuntime._apply_option_overrides` SHALL update `agent_name` to \"new-name\"\n131: \n132: ### Scenario: Override Language\n133: \n134: - **GIVEN** metadata exists with `language = \"python\"`\n135: - **WHEN** CLI option `--language java` is provided\n136: - **THEN** the system SHALL update `language` to \"java\" and validate Java workspace compatibility\n137: \n138: ### Scenario: Override Entrypoint\n139: \n140: - **GIVEN** metadata exists with `entrypoint = \"python main.py\"`\n141: - **WHEN** CLI option `--entrypoint \"python app.py\"` is provided\n142: - **THEN** the system SHALL update `entrypoint` to \"python app.py\"\n143: \n144: ### Scenario: Override Port\n145: \n146: - **GIVEN** metadata exists with `port = 8080`\n147: - **WHEN** CLI option `--port 9000` is provided\n148: - **THEN** the system SHALL update `port` to `9000` and validate the port range `1..65535`\n149: \n150: ### Scenario: Override Build Mode\n151: \n152: - **GIVEN** metadata exists with `build_mode = \"local\"`\n153: - **WHEN** CLI option `--build-mode cloud` is provided\n154: - **THEN** the system SHALL update `build_mode` to \"cloud\"\n155: \n156: ### Scenario: Override Description\n157: \n158: - **GIVEN** metadata exists with `description = None`\n159: - **WHEN** CLI option `--description \"My AI agent\"` is provided\n160: - **THEN** the system SHALL update `description` to \"My AI agent\"\n161: \n162: ---\n163: \n164: ## Requirement: Language Compatibility Validation\n165: \n166: The system SHALL validate workspace compatibility with the specified or inferred language.\n167: \n168: ### Scenario: Validate Python Workspace Structure\n169: \n170: - **GIVEN** `metadata.language == \"python\"`\n171: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._validate_python_compatibility` runs\n172: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n173:   - Check for presence of at least one `*.py` file\n174:   - Optionally check for `requirements.txt` or `pyproject.toml`\n175:   - Raise `ValueError` if Python files are missing\n176: \n177: ### Scenario: Validate Java Workspace Structure\n178: \n179: - **GIVEN** `metadata.language == \"java\"`\n180: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._validate_java_compatibility` runs\n181: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n182:   - Check for presence of `pom.xml`\n183:   - Raise `ValueError` if `pom.xml` is missing\n184: \n185: ### Scenario: Invalid Language Value\n186: \n187: - **GIVEN** CLI option `--language ruby` is provided\n188: - **WHEN** metadata is validated\n189: - **THEN** Pydantic SHALL raise validation error because `language` must be `python` or `java` (lowercase)\n190: \n191: ---\n192: \n193: ## Requirement: Entrypoint Inference\n194: \n195: The system SHALL infer the entrypoint command based on language and workspace contents when not explicitly provided.\n196: \n197: ### Scenario: Infer Python Entrypoint from main.py\n198: \n199: - **GIVEN** `language = \"python\"` and `entrypoint` is not provided\n200: - **WHEN** `main.py` exists in the workspace\n201: - **THEN** `PackRuntime._infer_entrypoint` SHALL return `\"python main.py\"`\n202: \n203: ### Scenario: Infer Python Entrypoint from app.py\n204: \n205: - **GIVEN** `language = \"python\"` and `entrypoint` is not provided and `main.py` does not exist\n206: - **WHEN** `app.py` exists in the workspace\n207: - **THEN** the system SHALL infer `\"python app.py\"`\n208: \n209: ### Scenario: Infer Python Entrypoint from First py File\n210: \n211: - **GIVEN** `language = \"python\"` and neither `main.py` nor `app.py` exist\n212: - **WHEN** other `*.py` files exist (e.g., `agent.py`)\n213: - **THEN** the system SHALL infer `\"python {first_py_file}\"`\n214: \n215: ### Scenario: Infer Java Entrypoint\n216: \n217: - **GIVEN** `language = \"java\"` and `entrypoint` is not provided\n218: - **WHEN** `pom.xml` exists\n219: - **THEN** the system SHALL infer a Maven-based entrypoint (e.g., `\"java -jar target/*.jar\"` or appropriate command)\n220: \n221: ---\n222: \n223: ## Requirement: Dependency Processing\n224: \n225: The system SHALL process language-specific dependencies and prepare them for containerization.\n226: \n227: ### Scenario: Process Python Dependencies from requirements.txt\n228: \n229: - **GIVEN** `language = \"python\"` and `requirements.txt` exists\n230: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._process_python_dependencies` runs\n231: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n232:   - Copy `requirements.txt` to the packaging context\n233:   - Record `requirements_file` in metadata as `\"requirements.txt\"`\n234: \n235: ### Scenario: Process Python Dependencies from pyproject.toml\n236: \n237: - **GIVEN** `language = \"python\"` and `pyproject.toml` exists (no `requirements.txt`)\n238: - **WHEN** dependency processing runs\n239: - **THEN** the system SHALL handle `pyproject.toml` based dependencies\n240: \n241: ### Scenario: Process Java Dependencies from pom.xml\n242: \n243: - **GIVEN** `language = \"java\"` and `pom.xml` exists\n244: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._process_java_dependencies` runs\n245: - **THEN** the system SHALL copy `pom.xml` and prepare Maven build context\n246: \n247: ---\n248: \n249: ## Requirement: Dockerfile Generation\n250: \n251: The system SHALL generate a language-appropriate Dockerfile when one does not exist in the workspace.\n252: \n253: ### Scenario: Generate Python Dockerfile\n254: \n255: - **GIVEN** `language = \"python\"` and no existing Dockerfile\n256: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._generate_python_dockerfile` runs\n257: - **THEN** the generated Dockerfile SHALL:\n258:   - Use a Python base image (e.g., `python:3.10-slim`)\n259:   - Install dependencies from `requirements.txt` if present\n260:   - Copy source files\n261:   - Set the entrypoint from metadata\n262:   - Expose the port from metadata\n263: \n264: ### Scenario: Generate Java Dockerfile\n265: \n266: - **GIVEN** `language = \"java\"` and no existing Dockerfile\n267: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._generate_java_dockerfile` runs\n268: - **THEN** the generated Dockerfile SHALL:\n269:   - Use a Maven/Java base image (multi-stage build)\n270:   - Build from `pom.xml`\n271:   - Copy the built JAR\n272:   - Set the entrypoint from metadata\n273:   - Expose the port from metadata\n274: \n275: ### Scenario: Skip Dockerfile Generation if Exists\n276: \n277: - **GIVEN** a `Dockerfile` already exists in the workspace\n278: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._generate_dockerfile` runs\n279: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n280:   - Not overwrite the existing Dockerfile\n281:   - Return `None` or the path to the existing Dockerfile\n282:   - Log that existing Dockerfile will be used\n283: \n284: ### Scenario: Dockerfile Path Update in Metadata\n285: \n286: - **GIVEN** a Dockerfile is generated or exists\n287: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._update_pack_metadata` runs\n288: - **THEN** the metadata SHALL be updated with Dockerfile path reference\n289: \n290: ---\n291: \n292: ## Requirement: Output Path Preparation\n293: \n294: The system SHALL prepare the output path for packaging when specified.\n295: \n296: ### Scenario: Use Specified Output Path\n297: \n298: - **GIVEN** CLI option `--output /path/to/output.tar.gz` is provided\n299: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._prepare_output_path` runs\n300: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n301:   - Validate the parent directory exists\n302:   - Return the absolute path for the output archive\n303: \n304: ### Scenario: Default Output Path\n305: \n306: - **GIVEN** `--output` is not specified\n307: - **WHEN** output path is prepared\n308: - **THEN** the system SHALL use a default output location based on workspace (e.g., `{workspace}/{agent_name}-packaged.tar.gz`)\n309: \n310: ### Scenario: Create Output Parent Directory\n311: \n312: - **GIVEN** output path parent directory does not exist\n313: - **WHEN** output path is prepared\n314: - **THEN** the system SHALL create the parent directory\n315: \n316: ---\n317: \n318: ## Requirement: Metadata Schema Validation\n319: \n320: The system SHALL validate metadata against the `AgentMetadata` Pydantic model.\n321: \n322: ### Scenario: Valid Metadata Fields\n323: \n324: - **GIVEN** metadata YAML is loaded\n325: - **WHEN** `AgentMetadata` model validation runs\n326: - **THEN** all fields SHALL conform to their types and constraints:\n327:   - `agent_name` is required `str`\n328:   - `language` is `str` with validator allowing only `python` or `java` (lowercase)\n329:   - `port` is `int` in range `1..65535`\n330:   - `build_mode` is `str` with validator allowing only `local` or `cloud` (lowercase)\n331: \n332: ### Scenario: Invalid Language Rejected\n333: \n334: - **GIVEN** metadata contains `language = \"ruby\"`\n335: - **WHEN** Pydantic validation runs\n336: - **THEN** the validator SHALL raise `ValidationError` indicating language must be `python` or `java`\n337: \n338: ### Scenario: Invalid Port Range Rejected\n339: \n340: - **GIVEN** metadata contains `port = 70000`\n341: - **WHEN** Pydantic validation runs\n342: - **THEN** the validator SHALL raise `ValidationError` indicating port must be in range `1..65535`\n343: \n344: ### Scenario: Invalid Build Mode Rejected\n345: \n346: - **GIVEN** metadata contains `build_mode = \"docker\"`\n347: - **WHEN** Pydantic validation runs\n348: - **THEN** the validator SHALL raise `ValidationError` indicating build_mode must be `local` or `cloud`\n349: \n350: ---\n351: \n352: ## Requirement: Metadata Save Location\n353: \n354: The system SHALL persist metadata as YAML in a canonical location.\n355: \n356: ### Scenario: Save Metadata to Canonical Path\n357: \n358: - **GIVEN** metadata is updated during pack\n359: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.save_metadata` runs\n360: - **THEN** the file SHALL be written to `{workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml` using:\n361:   - `yaml.dump` with `default_flow_style=False`\n362:   - `indent=2`\n363:   - `sort_keys=False`\n364:   - `model_dump(exclude_none=True)` to exclude None fields\n365: \n366: ---\n367: \n368: ## Requirement: Pack Result Structure\n369: \n370: The system SHALL return a structured result from `PackRuntime.pack`.\n371: \n372: ### Scenario: Return Pack Result Dictionary\n373: \n374: - **GIVEN** `PackRuntime.pack` completes successfully\n375: - **WHEN** the method returns\n376: - **THEN** the result SHALL be a `Dict[str, Any]` containing:\n377:   - `agent_name`: the resolved agent name\n378:   - `workspace_path`: absolute path to the workspace\n379:   - `metadata_path`: path to the saved metadata file\n380:   - `dockerfile_path`: path to generated or existing Dockerfile (or `None`)\n381:   - `language`: the resolved language\n382:   - `entrypoint`: the resolved entrypoint command\n383:   - `port`: the resolved port number\n384: \n385: ---\n386: \n387: ## Requirement: Global Verbose Logging on Pack\n388: \n389: The system SHALL enable verbose logging when `--verbose` is passed to the pack command.\n390: \n391: ### Scenario: Verbose Logging Enabled\n392: \n393: - **GIVEN** the user passes `--verbose` to the pack command\n394: - **WHEN** the pack command runs\n395: - **THEN** `PackRuntime` SHALL:\n396:   - Set `verbose=True` in the runtime constructor\n397:   - Log detailed progress messages during each step\n398:   - Include file paths and intermediate results in logs\n399: \n400: ---\n401: \n402: ## Requirement: PackRuntime Initialization\n403: \n404: The system SHALL construct `PackRuntime` with appropriate configuration.\n405: \n406: ### Scenario: PackRuntime Constructor\n407: \n408: - **GIVEN** `PackRuntime(verbose=False)` is constructed\n409: - **WHEN** the instance is created\n410: - **THEN** the runtime SHALL:\n411:   - Initialize `MetadataService` for metadata operations\n412:   - Initialize `DockerService` if Docker integration is needed\n413:   - Store the `verbose` flag for logging control\n414: \n415: ---\n416: \n417: ## Requirement: MetadataOptions Conversion\n418: \n419: The system SHALL convert CLI options to `MetadataOptions` dataclass.\n420: \n421: ### Scenario: Convert Options to MetadataOptions\n422: \n423: - **GIVEN** CLI options dict with keys matching `MetadataOptions` fields\n424: - **WHEN** `MetadataOptions.from_options(options)` runs\n425: - **THEN** the system SHALL create a `MetadataOptions` instance with:\n426:   - All optional fields populated from corresponding option values\n427:   - Defaults applied for missing optional fields per dataclass definition\n428: \n429: ---\n430: \n431: ## Requirement: Pack Command Error Display\n432: \n433: The system SHALL display errors appropriately based on verbose mode.\n434: \n435: ### Scenario: Display Error with Traceback in Verbose Mode\n436: \n437: - **GIVEN** an exception occurs during pack and `verbose=True`\n438: - **WHEN** `_handle_error` is called\n439: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL:\n440:   - Print `Error packaging agent: {exception_message}` in red via Rich\n441:   - Print the full Python traceback\n442:   - Call `typer.Exit(1)` to terminate\n443: \n444: ### Scenario: Display Error Without Traceback in Non-Verbose Mode\n445: \n446: - **GIVEN** an exception occurs during pack and `verbose=False`\n447: - **WHEN** `_handle_error` is called\n448: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL:\n449:   - Print `Error packaging agent: {exception_message}` in red via Rich\n450:   - NOT print traceback\n451:   - Call `typer.Exit(1)` to terminate\n452: \n453: ---\n454: \n455: ## Requirement: Workspace Path Resolution\n456: \n457: The system SHALL resolve the workspace path to an absolute path.\n458: \n459: ### Scenario: Resolve Relative Workspace Path\n460: \n461: - **GIVEN** `workspace = \".\"` (relative path)\n462: - **WHEN** the pack command processes the workspace\n463: - **THEN** the system SHALL resolve it to an absolute path using `Path(workspace).resolve()`\n464: \n465: ### Scenario: Resolve Absolute Workspace Path\n466: \n467: - **GIVEN** `workspace = \"/home/user/my-agent\"` (absolute path)\n468: - **WHEN** the pack command processes the workspace\n469: - **THEN** the system SHALL use the path as-is or normalize it\n470: \n471: ---\n472: \n473: ## Requirement: Progress Indicator During Pack\n474: \n475: The system SHALL display a progress spinner during pack operations.\n476: \n477: ### Scenario: Rich Progress Spinner Display\n478: \n479: - **GIVEN** the pack command is executing\n480: - **WHEN** operations like metadata loading, validation, and Dockerfile generation run\n481: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL display a Rich Progress spinner with descriptive text (e.g., \"Packaging agent...\")\n482: \n483: ---\n484: \n485: ## Requirement: Multi-File Workspace Handling\n486: \n487: The system SHALL handle workspaces with multiple source files appropriately.\n488: \n489: ### Scenario: Python Workspace with Multiple Files\n490: \n491: - **GIVEN** a Python workspace with `main.py`, `utils.py`, `config.py`, and `requirements.txt`\n492: - **WHEN** pack runs\n493: - **THEN** the system SHALL:\n494:   - Identify all `.py` files for validation\n495:   - Copy all source files to the packaging context\n496:   - Include `requirements.txt` in dependency processing\n497: \n498: ---\n499: \n500: ## Requirement: Pack Command Help Text\n501: \n502: The system SHALL provide help text for all pack command options.\n503: \n504: ### Scenario: Pack Command Help Display\n505: \n506: - **GIVEN** the user runs `pack --help`\n507: - **WHEN** the help is displayed\n508: - **THEN** Typer SHALL show:\n509:   - Command description\n510:   - All options with their names, types, defaults, and help strings\n511:   - Usage examples if configured\n512: \n513: ---\n514: \n515: ## Implementation Files\n516: \n517: | File | Purpose |\n518: |------|---------|\n519: | `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Typer `pack` command definition |\n520: | `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py` | `PackRuntime` implementation |\n521: | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | `MetadataService` for metadata operations |\n522: | `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` | `MetadataOptions` dataclass |\n523: \n524: ---\n525: \n526: ## Dependencies\n527: \n528: | Package | Purpose |\n529: |---------|---------|\n530: | `typer[all]>=0.9.0` | CLI framework with Rich integration |\n531: | `pydantic>=2.0.0` | Metadata model validation |\n532: | `pyyaml>=6.0` | YAML metadata file handling |\n533: | `rich>=13.0.0` | Progress spinner and error display |\n534: | `pathlib` | Path resolution and validation |\n535: \n536: ---\n537: \n538: ## Validation Checklist\n539: \n540: - [ ] Pack command registered in Typer app with correct options\n541: - [ ] Options have correct types and defaults matching spec\n542: - [ ] Workspace validation checks existence and directory type\n543: - [ ] Language-specific file validation for Python and Java\n544: - [ ] Metadata loaded from `agent_metadata.yaml` with fallbacks\n545: - [ ] New metadata created with defaults when file missing\n546: - [ ] CLI option overrides applied to metadata\n547: - [ ] Entrypoint inferred based on language and files\n548: - [ ] Dockerfile generated with language-specific template\n549: - [ ] Existing Dockerfile not overwritten\n550: - [ ] Metadata saved to canonical path with correct YAML format\n551: - [ ] Pack result returns structured dictionary\n552: - [ ] Verbose mode enables detailed logging\n553: - [ ] Error handling prints traceback in verbose mode\n554: - [ ] Rich Progress spinner displayed during execution\n555: - [ ] Pydantic validation rejects invalid language/port/build_mode\n\n(End of file - total 555 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Specification — CLI pack Command\n\nAR: AR-020 — CLI pack 命令\nModule: cmd/cli\nLanguage: Python\nSize: M\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Pack Command Entry Point\n\nThe system SHALL provide a `pack` subcommand via Typer application to validate and prepare a workspace, merge CLI overrides into metadata, optionally generate a Dockerfile, and report paths.\n\n### Scenario: Options and Defaults\n\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `pack` without specifying any options\n- **WHEN** the command is invoked\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL use the following defaults:\n  - `workspace` = \".\" (`-f` / `--workspace`, type `str`)\n  - `agent_name` = `None` (`--agent-name`, type `Optional[str]`)","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775876761037,"end":1775876761054}}}}
